---
description: Enforce the arena shooter source layout from the start.
alwaysApply: true
---

Use this project structure for all new code unless the user explicitly approves a change:

```text
src/
  app/
    App.tsx
    routes/
    providers/
  game/
    config/
    core/
      gameLoop/
      state/
      events/
      timing/
    renderer/
      canvas/
      lighting/
      postfx/
      materials/
      webgpu/
    world/
      map/
      props/
      spawn/
      navigation/
    player/
      controller/
      camera/
      weapons/
      inventory/
      health/
    enemies/
      types/
      ai/
      spawning/
      combat/
    pickups/
      weaponPads/
      health/
      armor/
      ammo/
    ui/
      hud/
      menus/
      overlays/
      crosshair/
    audio/
    assets/
      models/
      textures/
      audio/
  shared/
    types/
    utils/
    constants/
```

Placement rules:

- Keep React app composition, routes, and providers under `src/app`.
- Keep gameplay code under `src/game`.
- Keep reusable cross-cutting types, constants, and utilities under `src/shared`.
- Do not create new top-level folders under `src` without explicit approval.
- Do not place renderer, world, player, enemy, pickup, or UI gameplay systems outside their matching `src/game/*` domains.
- When adding a new file, choose the most specific existing folder first instead of creating a parallel structure.
